markets.title: Will Tim Echols win the the 2025 Georgia Public Service Commission District 2 election?
markets.subtitle: :: Republican
markets.rules_primary: If Tim Echols wins the 2025 Georgia Public Service Commission District 2 election, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: The market resolves based on the official certification or declaration by the relevant electoral authority. For parliamentary elections, the party or coalition with the most seats wins unless a different party forms government through coalition. For referendums, "Yes" and "No" are the options. For presidential or direct elections, the candidate who wins according to the electoral system (electoral college, popular vote, or runoff as applicable) is the winner. Markets resolve based on official results, not exit polls or projections. If elections are postponed beyond the expiration date, markets resolve to No. Contested results are resolved based on the final certified outcome by the appropriate electoral authority or highest court with jurisdiction.
markets.early_close_condition: This market will close and expire early if the election winner is officially declared or certified.
